+      <img class="brand-logo logo-light" src="/assets/images/logo-black-light.png" alt="Who’s to Say ? Foundation logo (light)" />
+    </a>
+    <nav class="site-nav" aria-label="Primary navigation">
+      <a class="nav-link" data-nav="home" href="/">Home</a>
+      <div class="nav-item has-submenu" data-submenu="programs">
+        <a class="nav-link" data-nav="programs" href="/programs.html" aria-haspopup="true" aria-expanded="false">Programs</a>
+        <div class="nav-submenu" role="menu" aria-label="Programs submenu">
+          <a class="submenu-link" role="menuitem" href="/programs/digital-content-creator.html">Digital Path</a>
+          <a class="submenu-link" role="menuitem" href="/programs/whos-to-say-sports.html">Sports Path</a>
+          <a class="submenu-link" role="menuitem" href="/programs/life-skills-independent-living.html">Independence Path</a>
+          <a class="submenu-link" role="menuitem" href="/programs/community-integration-advocacy.html">Community Path</a>
+          <a class="submenu-link" role="menuitem" href="/programs/maker-market-events.html">Art Path</a>
+          <a class="submenu-link" role="menuitem" href="/programs/entertainment-pathways.html">Entertainment Path</a>
+        </div>
+      </div>
+      <a class="nav-link active" aria-current="page" href="/creative-workshops.html">Creative Workshops</a>
+      <a class="nav-link" href="https://givebutter.com/whostosayfoundation" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Donate</a>
+      <a class="nav-link" href="/contact.html">Contact</a>
+    </nav>
+    <div class="header-actions">
+      <button class="theme-toggle" type="button" aria-label="Toggle theme" aria-pressed="false"></button>
+    </div>
+  </div>
+</header>
+
+<main id="main">
+
+  <!-- HERO -->
+  <section class="programs-hero programs-hero--image" aria-label="Creative Workshops introduction">
+    <div class="programs-wrapper hero-inner">
+      <p class="home-kicker">Public Creative Workshops</p>
+      <h1>Creative media, storytelling, and maker experiences for people of all ages and abilities.</h1>
+      <p>
+        Who’s to Say? offers public creative workshops, private creative coaching, and project-based studio sessions
+        where participants can explore photography, video, music, gaming, design, sports media, storytelling, legacy
+        projects, and hands-on creative builds.
+      </p>
+      <p>
+        Our sessions are interest-driven, welcoming, and built around real creative work — helping each person build
+        confidence, communication, technical skills, connection, and a stronger sense of what is possible.
+      </p>
+      <div class="btn-row">
+        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="#workshop-menu">Explore Workshops</a>
+        <a class="btn btn-secondary" href="/contact.html">Contact Us</a>
+      </div>
+    </div>
+  </section>
+
+  <!-- OPEN TO THE PUBLIC -->
+  <section class="programs-wrapper" aria-label="Open to the public">
+    <div class="divider-ribbon">
+      <span class="divider-ribbon__line" aria-hidden="true"></span>
+      <h2>Creative opportunities open to the community.</h2>
+      <span class="divider-ribbon__line" aria-hidden="true"></span>
+    </div>
+    <div class="program-section">
+      <p>
+        Who’s to Say? is building a creative studio model that welcomes people of all ages and abilities. Our workshops
+        and private sessions are available to the general public and can be adapted around each participant’s interests,
+        experience level, communication style, and creative goals.
+      </p>
+      <p>
+        Some people come to learn a specific tool. Some come to build confidence. Some want to tell their story, create
+        content, explore music, document sports, preserve family memories, design something original, or simply try a
+        new creative experience in a supportive environment.
+      </p>
+      <p>
+        We are especially interested in creative projects that bring generations together — helping older adults
+        preserve stories, photos, music, and memories while giving younger creators and participants meaningful roles in
+        capturing, designing, editing, and sharing those stories.
+      </p>
+      <p>The common thread is simple: creativity without comparison.</p>
+    </div>
+  </section>
+
+  <!-- WORKSHOP MENU -->
+  <section class="programs-wrapper" id="workshop-menu" aria-label="Workshop menu">
+    <div class="divider-ribbon">
+      <span class="divider-ribbon__line" aria-hidden="true"></span>
+      <h2>Workshop and studio session options</h2>
+      <span class="divider-ribbon__line" aria-hidden="true"></span>
+    </div>
+    <p class="how-sub">
+      Sessions may be offered as private creative coaching, small-group workshops, family-supported projects,
+      intergenerational storytelling sessions, community workshops, or customized studio blocks depending on the
+      participant’s goals and the type of creative work involved.
+    </p>
+    <div class="program-grid">
+      <div class="program-card">
+        <div class="card-content">
+          <span class="program-label">Storytelling</span>
+          <h3>Digital Storytelling</h3>
+          <p>Plan, record, edit, and share personal stories through video, photos, captions, voice, and simple publishing workflows.</p>
+        </div>
+      </div>
+      <div class="program-card">
+        <div class="card-content">
+          <span class="program-label">Photography</span>
+          <h3>Photography &amp; Visual Storytelling</h3>
+          <p>Learn how to capture images, choose favorites, edit photos, build galleries, and tell a story through a visual collection.</p>
+        </div>
+      </div>
+      <div class="program-card">
+        <div class="card-content">
+          <span class="program-label">Legacy</span>
+          <h3>Legacy Story Lab</h3>
+          <p>Bring old photos, family memories, favorite songs, life stories, or local history and turn them into short videos, digital albums, captions, interviews, or keepsake projects.</p>
+        </div>
+      </div>
+      <div class="program-card">
+        <div class="card-content">
+          <span class="program-label">Audio</span>
+          <h3>Podcasting &amp; Voice</h3>
+          <p>Explore microphones, interview questions, short scripts, voice recordings, show ideas, and simple audio production.</p>
+        </div>
+      </div>
+      <div class="program-card">
+        <div class="card-content">
+          <span class="program-label">Music</span>
+          <h3>Music &amp; DJ-Style Media</h3>
+          <p>Create playlists, radio-style intros, music stories, artist spotlights, and short audio segments built around personal music interests and memories.</p>
+        </div>
+      </div>
+      <div class="program-card">
+        <div class="card-content">
+          <span class="program-label">Gaming</span>
+          <h3>Gaming &amp; Streaming Content</h3>
+          <p>Develop creator-style content around favorite games, including commentary, short clips, stream layouts, thumbnails, and safe publishing habits.</p>
+        </div>
+      </div>
+      <div class="program-card">
+        <div class="card-content">
+          <span class="program-label">Sports Media</span>
+          <h3>Sports Media</h3>
+          <p>Create sports coverage through photos, interviews, recap videos, player spotlights, score graphics, local sports memories, and community event storytelling.</p>
+        </div>
+      </div>
+      <div class="program-card">
+        <div class="card-content">
+          <span class="program-label">Design</span>
+          <h3>Design, Canva &amp; Creator Tools</h3>
+          <p>Use accessible digital tools to create posters, social graphics, cards, simple brand assets, photo layouts, and project designs.</p>
+        </div>
+      </div>
+      <div class="program-card">
+        <div class="card-content">
+          <span class="program-label">Maker</span>
+          <h3>Maker Projects &amp; Creative Builds</h3>
+          <p>Explore hands-on creative projects using digital design, upcycled materials, simple fabrication, merch concepts, and project-based making.</p>
+        </div>
+      </div>
+      <div class="program-card">
+        <div class="card-content">
+          <span class="program-label">Intergenerational</span>
+          <h3>Intergenerational Media Projects</h3>
+          <p>Create shared projects that connect seniors, families, students, creators, and people of all abilities through stories, photos, music, interviews, and community memory projects.</p>
+        </div>
+      </div>
+    </div>
+  </section>
+
+  <!-- FLEXIBLE WAYS TO PARTICIPATE -->
+  <section class="programs-wrapper" id="pricing" aria-label="Flexible ways to participate">
+    <div class="divider-ribbon">
+      <span class="divider-ribbon__line" aria-hidden="true"></span>
+      <h2>Flexible ways to participate</h2>
+      <span class="divider-ribbon__line" aria-hidden="true"></span>
+    </div>
+    <p class="how-sub">
+      Who’s to Say? offers a mix of low-cost public workshops, private creative coaching, project-based studio sessions,
+      and donor-supported access opportunities. Pricing depends on the session type, length, materials, equipment,
+      preparation, travel, and project scope.
+    </p>
+    <p class="how-sub">The examples below are public-facing starting points and may vary depending on the project.</p>
+
+    <div class="how-grid how-grid--4">
+      <div class="how-card">
+        <h3>Community Workshops</h3>
+        <p class="rate-price">$25–$75</p>
+        <p>Lower-cost public workshops, drop-in creative experiences, community events, or introductory sessions focused on one activity, tool, or project theme.</p>
+      </div>
+      <div class="how-card">
+        <h3>Private Creative Coaching</h3>
+        <p class="rate-price">$95–$175</p>
+        <p>Focused one-on-one creative sessions built around the participant’s interests, project goals, learning style, and preferred creative tools.</p>
+      </div>
+      <div class="how-card">
+        <h3>Extended Project Studio Sessions</h3>
+        <p class="rate-price">$225–$300</p>
+        <p>Longer project-based studio sessions for deeper creative work such as recording, editing, photography, design, sports media, storytelling, or maker projects.</p>
+      </div>
+      <div class="how-card">
+        <h3>Memberships &amp; Sponsored Access</h3>
+        <p class="rate-price">Coming soon</p>
+        <p>Our next phase includes community memberships, sponsored workshops, donor-supported scholarships, and studio access options that help make creative tools available to more people.</p>
+      </div>
+    </div>
+
+    <p class="cw-note">
+      Rates may vary based on session length, materials, preparation, travel, equipment needs, and project scope. Some
+      community workshops may be free, donation-based, sponsored, or scholarship-supported.
+      <a href="/contact.html">Contact us</a> for current availability and the best fit for your project.
+    </p>
+  </section>
+
+  <!-- HOW SESSIONS WORK -->
+  <section class="how-pathways" aria-label="How sessions work">
+    <div class="programs-wrapper">
+      <div class="divider-ribbon">
+        <span class="divider-ribbon__line" aria-hidden="true"></span>
+        <h2>How sessions work</h2>
+        <span class="divider-ribbon__line" aria-hidden="true"></span>
+      </div>
+      <div class="how-grid how-grid--4">
+        <div class="how-card">
+          <div class="how-icon" aria-hidden="true">1</div>
+          <h3>Choose a creative direction</h3>
+          <p>Start with an interest, story, tool, project idea, event, memory, or creative goal.</p>
+        </div>
+        <div class="how-card">
+          <div class="how-icon" aria-hidden="true">2</div>
+          <h3>Plan the session</h3>
+          <p>We shape the session around the participant’s goals, communication style, comfort level, creative interests, and project needs.</p>
+        </div>
+        <div class="how-card">
+          <div class="how-icon" aria-hidden="true">3</div>
+          <h3>Create together</h3>
+          <p>Participants explore tools, make creative decisions, practice skills, and build something real.</p>
+        </div>
+        <div class="how-card">
+          <div class="how-icon" aria-hidden="true">4</div>
+          <h3>Share or continue</h3>
+          <p>Projects can become galleries, videos, graphics, audio segments, portfolios, family keepsakes, community stories, or future workshop ideas.</p>
+        </div>
+      </div>
+    </div>
+  </section>
+
+  <!-- INCLUSIVE AND INTERGENERATIONAL BY DESIGN -->
+  <section class="programs-wrapper" aria-label="Inclusive and intergenerational by design">
+    <div class="divider-ribbon">
+      <span class="divider-ribbon__line" aria-hidden="true"></span>
+      <h2>Inclusive and intergenerational by design</h2>
+      <span class="divider-ribbon__line" aria-hidden="true"></span>
+    </div>
+    <div class="program-section">
+      <p>
+        Who’s to Say? was built around the belief that creativity should not be limited by comparison, labels, age,
+        confidence, or low expectations. We welcome people with different learning styles, communication styles, support
+        needs, life experiences, and creative backgrounds.
+      </p>
+      <p>
+        Our approach is flexible, patient, practical, and project-based. We focus on helping each person participate
+        meaningfully, make choices, use real tools, and experience the pride of creating something that reflects who
+        they are.
+      </p>
+      <p>
+        We also believe communities are stronger when people of different generations have a place to create together.
+        Seniors may bring stories, photos, music, memories, and local history. Younger creators and participants may
+        bring energy, curiosity, technical tools, and new ways to share. The studio becomes the bridge.
+      </p>
+    </div>
+  </section>
+
+  <!-- FUNDING NOTE -->
+  <section class="programs-wrapper" id="funding" aria-label="Using approved funding sources">
+    <div class="divider-ribbon">
+      <span class="divider-ribbon__line" aria-hidden="true"></span>
+      <h2>Using approved funding sources</h2>
+      <span class="divider-ribbon__line" aria-hidden="true"></span>
+    </div>
+    <div class="program-section">
+      <p>
+        Families using self-directed budgets, third-party funding, grants, scholarships, or other approved funding
+        sources may be able to use those funds for Who’s to Say? workshops or private creative sessions when the service
+        is approved through the individual’s plan or funding source.
+      </p>
+      <p>
+        We can provide general descriptions, session summaries, invoices, and supporting documentation upon request.
+        Approval decisions are made by the applicable funding source, plan, or reviewer.
+      </p>
+      <div class="btn-row">
+        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="/support-coordinators.html">Information for Support Coordinators</a>
+      </div>
+    </div>
+  </section>
+
+  <!-- BUILDING TOWARD A COMMUNITY DIGITAL MEDIA & MAKER SPACE -->
+  <section class="programs-wrapper" aria-label="Building the next phase">
+    <div class="divider-ribbon">
+      <span class="divider-ribbon__line" aria-hidden="true"></span>
+      <h2>Building the next phase: a community creative space.</h2>
+      <span class="divider-ribbon__line" aria-hidden="true"></span>
+    </div>
+    <div class="program-section">
+      <p>
+        Today, Who’s to Say? offers creative workshops, private coaching, intergenerational storytelling, and
+        project-based studio sessions. Our next phase is to grow this work into a community-centered digital media and
+        maker space — a welcoming place where people of different ages, abilities, backgrounds, and life experiences can
+        create, collaborate, learn modern tools, and share their stories.
+      </p>
+      <p>
+        This future space will support digital storytelling, photography, video, music, gaming, design, maker projects,
+        community exhibits, sports media, creator workshops, family legacy projects, photo digitizing, accessible
+        technology experiences, and intergenerational community memory projects.
+      </p>
+      <p>
+        Funds raised through donations, sponsorships, grants, memberships, and community partnerships will help us
+        expand access to equipment, studio space, adaptive tools, creative technology, workshops, scholarships, and
+        community programming.
+      </p>
+      <div class="btn-row">
+        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="https://givebutter.com/whostosayfoundation" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Help Build the Studio</a>
+        <a class="btn btn-secondary" href="/contact.html">Contact Us</a>
+      </div>
+    </div>
+  </section>
+
+  <!-- FINAL CTA -->
+  <section class="how-pathways" aria-label="Start a conversation">
+    <div class="programs-wrapper cw-cta">
+      <div class="divider-ribbon">
+        <span class="divider-ribbon__line" aria-hidden="true"></span>
+        <h2>Have a project, participant, class, family story, or community idea in mind?</h2>
+        <span class="divider-ribbon__line" aria-hidden="true"></span>
+      </div>
+      <p class="how-sub">
+        We would love to hear what you are hoping to create. Contact us to discuss workshop availability, private
+        creative coaching, intergenerational storytelling, community partnerships, sponsored access, or ways to support
+        the next phase of Who’s to Say?.
+      </p>
+      <div class="btn-row">
+        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="/contact.html">Start a Conversation</a>
+      </div>
+    </div>
+  </section>
+
+</main>
+
+<footer class="site-footer">© <span id="year"></span> Who’s to Say ? Foundation</footer>
+<script>
+  (function () {
+    var el = document.getElementById("year");
+    if (el) el.textContent = new Date().getFullYear();
+  })();
+</script>
+</body>
+</html>
