+        </div>
+        <p class="home-kicker">Support Coordinator Information</p>
+        <h1>Creative workshop descriptions and documentation for plan review.</h1>
+        <p class="program-subtitle">
+          Who’s to Say? offers public creative workshops, private creative coaching, intergenerational storytelling, and
+          project-based studio sessions focused on creative media, storytelling, digital tools, communication,
+          confidence, and community participation.
+        </p>
+        <p class="program-subtitle">
+          This page provides general language that families and Support Coordinators may use when considering whether a
+          workshop or session may be appropriate for an individual’s plan or funding source.
+        </p>
+        <div class="btn-row">
+          <a class="btn btn-primary" href="/creative-workshops.html">View Creative Workshops</a>
+          <a class="btn btn-secondary" href="/contact.html">Contact Us</a>
+        </div>
+      </div>
+    </div>
+  </section>
+
+  <!-- 60/40 SHELL -->
+  <section class="program-shell program-shell--6040">
+    <article class="program-content">
+
+      <section class="program-section">
+        <h2>What Who’s to Say? provides</h2>
+        <p>
+          Who’s to Say? provides public creative media workshops and project-based studio sessions that can be
+          individualized around a participant’s interests, goals, preferred tools, and communication style.
+        </p>
+        <p>
+          Sessions may include activities such as photography, video creation, podcast-style recording, music and
+          playlist storytelling, sports media, gaming content, graphic design, creator tools, legacy storytelling,
+          photo digitizing, community memory projects, and hands-on maker projects.
+        </p>
+        <p>
+          The focus is on meaningful creative participation, communication, confidence, digital skill-building, project
+          completion, and community connection.
+        </p>
+      </section>
+
+      <section class="program-section">
+        <h2>Sample description language</h2>
+        <p>Families and Support Coordinators may adapt the following language when describing a session request or creative workshop goal.</p>
+
+        <h3>General creative workshop description</h3>
+        <p>
+          Public creative media workshop or private creative coaching session focused on digital storytelling, creative
+          skill-building, communication, confidence, and project-based participation through photography, video, music,
+          design, gaming, sports media, legacy storytelling, or maker activities.
+        </p>
+
+        <h3>Project-based studio description</h3>
+        <p>
+          Project-based creative studio session designed around the participant’s interests and goals, supporting
+          planning, creative decision-making, use of digital tools, communication, and completion of a tangible media
+          or maker project.
+        </p>
+
+        <h3>Community-centered creative participation</h3>
+        <p>
+          Inclusive creative workshop experience that supports participation in community-based media, storytelling,
+          design, photography, audio, video, or maker projects while building confidence, communication, and creative
+          independence.
+        </p>
+
+        <h3>Intergenerational storytelling description</h3>
+        <p>
+          Creative storytelling session focused on preserving stories, photos, music, memories, interviews, or community
+          history through digital media, captions, photo organization, audio, video, or simple design projects.
+        </p>
+      </section>
+
+      <section class="program-section">
+        <h2>Sample invoice language</h2>
+        <p>
+          When requested, invoices may describe the specific public workshop or creative session provided, including the
+          date, session type, rate, length, and project focus.
+        </p>
+        <ul>
+          <li>
+            Creative media workshop / private creative coaching session focused on project-based digital storytelling,
+            communication, creative skill-building, and use of media tools aligned with the participant’s approved goals
+            and interests.
+          </li>
+          <li>
+            Project-based studio session focused on photography, video, music, design, sports media, maker activities,
+            or legacy storytelling, including planning, creative decision-making, use of digital tools, and completion
+            of a media or creative project.
+          </li>
+        </ul>
+        <p class="cw-note">
+          Invoice language can be adjusted to accurately reflect the actual session provided, the approved plan
+          language, and the documentation needs of the family or funding source.
+        </p>
+      </section>
+
+      <section class="program-section">
+        <h2>Documentation available upon request</h2>
+        <p>Who’s to Say? can provide basic documentation to support review and recordkeeping, including:</p>
+        <ul>
+          <li>public workshop or session descriptions</li>
+          <li>invoices with date, rate, session type, and project focus</li>
+          <li>brief session summaries</li>
+          <li>examples of creative activities offered</li>
+          <li>general rate information</li>
+          <li>contact information for follow-up questions</li>
+        </ul>
+        <p>
+          Approval decisions are made by the applicable funding source, plan, or reviewer. We are happy to provide
+          accurate descriptions of the service offered and the creative work completed.
+        </p>
+      </section>
+
+      <section class="program-section">
+        <h2>Public access and funding review</h2>
+        <p>
+          Who’s to Say? workshops and private creative sessions are public-facing creative opportunities. They are
+          designed to be inclusive and accessible while remaining available to the broader community.
+        </p>
+        <p>
+          Families using self-directed budgets, third-party funding, grants, scholarships, or other approved funding
+          sources may be able to use those funds when the workshop or session is approved through the individual’s plan
+          or funding source.
+        </p>
+      </section>
+
+      <section class="program-section">
+        <h2>A growing community creative space</h2>
+        <p>
+          Who’s to Say? is also raising funds for the next phase of this work: a community-centered digital media and
+          maker space where people of different ages, abilities, backgrounds, and life experiences can create,
+          collaborate, learn modern tools, and share their stories.
+        </p>
+        <p>
+          This vision supports a broader public benefit — expanding access to creative technology, media tools,
+          workshops, studio experiences, intergenerational storytelling, digital literacy, family legacy projects, photo
+          preservation, community memory work, and accessible creative tools.
+        </p>
+      </section>
+
+      <section class="program-section cw-cta">
+        <h2>Need a description, invoice, or workshop explanation?</h2>
+        <p>
+          Families and Support Coordinators can contact us with questions about current workshop options, session
+          descriptions, documentation, rates, project ideas, or funding-source review needs.
+        </p>
+        <div class="btn-row">
+          <a class="btn btn-primary" href="/contact.html">Contact Who’s to Say?</a>
+        </div>
+      </section>
+
+    </article>
